thread.title: Jones makes return to girls basketball state final four Wednesday
thread.title_full: Jones makes return to girls basketball state final four Wednesday - Orlando Sentinel

author: orlandosentinel.com
title: Jones makes return to girls basketball state final four Wednesday
text:
Chardell Jones has had the hot hand for Jones entering Wednesday’s FHSAA Class 5A state semifinals.
The junior rounded out the regional tournament by averaging 16 points and eight rebounds in three games this month.
Included in that run was a stellar effort against two-time defending state champion Lake Highland Prep, where she finished with 19 points, 12 rebounds and six assists in a 52-49 semifinal win.
The Tigers face West Palm Beach Oxbridge Academy in a state semifinal at 4 p.m. Oxbridge, with a total of nine freshman and sophomores alongside just one senior, is appearing in its first final four.
The winner advances to Saturday’s title game at 10 a.m. against either Tallahassee Florida High or Fort Lauderdale Cardinal Gibbons.
Jones is in the state final four for the first time since losing in the semis in 2014, which capped the first season on the sideline for head coach Robert Moultrie.
It’s the eighth state tournament appearance for the program. Jones claimed titles in 1997 under the direction of Kelvin Harris and 2004 under Jimmy Mincey.
Sophomore Jamiya Turner averages 11.3 points and senior Shania Jacobs averages eight points per game for Jones.
Oxbridge Academy is led by the sophomore duo of Aaliyah Stanley (16.4 ppg) and Alexa Zaph (14.4 ppg).
